[length: 03:25.680]

[00:09.300] I smile in the mirror, but it cracks at the edge
[00:14.151] Comparing my shadow to someone else's ledge
[00:18.644] They’re louder, brighter, walking taller than I do
[00:23.230] And I shrink in the silence, just trying to break through
[00:27.668] I wear confidence like it’s borrowed for a day
[00:32.255] Folded at the seams, always slipping away
[00:37.606] I feel smaller than I should,
[00:41.581] Like I’m never enough, even when I’m good
[00:46.737] Living in the echo of someone else’s praise
[00:51.475] Trapped in the maze of my own sideways gaze
[00:55.916] But maybe there's more to me
[00:59.483] Than the doubt I let the world see
[01:09.975] I walk with a whisper while they run with a roar
[01:14.881] Measuring my worth by the cracks in the floor
[01:19.439] A thousand eyes and none of them mine
[01:24.150] Caught in a race where I fall behind
[01:28.260] Their stars burn loud while I fade to gray
[01:33.324] But I'm still here—won’t look away
[01:38.054] I feel smaller than I should,
[01:42.247] Like I’m never enough, even when I’m good
[01:47.519] Living in the echo of someone else’s praise
[01:52.136] Trapped in the maze of my own sideways gaze
[01:56.615] But maybe there's more to me
[02:00.046] Than the doubt I let the world see
[02:10.715] Every flaw I counted twice
[02:14.660] Was just a mirror bending light
[02:18.929] What if I’m not broken, just bruised?
[02:23.941] Not weak—just confused?
[02:29.412] I felt smaller than I should
[02:33.294] But maybe now, I’m learning I’m still good
[02:38.436] I’ll rise from the echo, find my own voice
[02:43.023] Stop seeing myself as the lesser choice
[02:47.669] 'Cause maybe there's strength in me
[02:51.291] That I never dared believe
[03:01.968] Echoes fade, but I'm still here
[03:06.449] Not quite loud, but I’m aware
[03:11.341] Every crack wrote my story
[03:16.000] Tracing proof that I survived